<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="458" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[131,776,1810,2028]" box="[132,232,1810,1836]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[131,776,1810,2028]" lastBlockId="6.[811,1457,1810,2028]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lamarck" authorityYear="1799" box="[245,360,1841,1867]" class="Gastropoda" family="Marginellidae" genus="Marginella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[245,360,1841,1867]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">Marginella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
typically includes species with brightly coloured shells, with a range of patterns (variously combined bands, flames, lineoles, blotches, dots, etc.) (
<bibRefCitation author="GOUD J. &amp; NEEFS J." pageId="6" pageNumber="457" pagination="25 - 50" refId="ref6984" refString="GOUD J. &amp; NEEFS J. 1996. - The larger marginelliform gastropods (Cystiscidae and Marginellidae) collected during the CANCAP and MAURITANIA expeditions in the southern part of the North Atlantic Ocean. The genera Persicula, Prunum, Dentimargo, Marginella and Glabella. Vita Marina 43 (3 - 4): 25 - 50." type="journal article" year="1996">Goud &amp; Neefs 1996</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="COSSIGNANI T." box="[206,396,1937,1964]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" refId="ref6349" refString="COSSIGNANI T. 2006. - Marginellidae and Cystiscidae of the World. Atlas with over 2,600 photos. L'Informatore Piceno, 408 p." type="book" year="2006">Cossignani 2006</bibRefCitation>
), but several colourless species are also known, mainly from deep waters (
<bibRefCitation author="BOUCHET P. &amp; WAREN A." pageId="6" pageNumber="457" pagination="123 - 296" refId="ref6057" refString="BOUCHET P. &amp; WAREN A. 1985. - Revision of the Northeast Atlantic bathyal and abyssal Neogastropoda excluding Turridae (Mollusca, Gastropoda). Bollettino Malacologico suppl. 1: 123 - 296." type="journal article" year="1985">Bouchet &amp; Warén 1985</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="GOUD J. &amp; NEEFS J." box="[202,419,2001,2028]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" pagination="25 - 50" refId="ref6984" refString="GOUD J. &amp; NEEFS J. 1996. - The larger marginelliform gastropods (Cystiscidae and Marginellidae) collected during the CANCAP and MAURITANIA expeditions in the southern part of the North Atlantic Ocean. The genera Persicula, Prunum, Dentimargo, Marginella and Glabella. Vita Marina 43 (3 - 4): 25 - 50." type="journal article" year="1996">Goud&amp; Neefs 1996</bibRefCitation>
). No preserved colour pattern was observed in the material of 
<taxonomicName authority="Perna &amp; Vazzana, 2016" authorityName="Perna &amp; Vazzana" authorityYear="2016" box="[1108,1243,1810,1835]" class="Gastropoda" family="Marginellidae" genus="Marginella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="seguenzai" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1108,1243,1810,1835]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">M. seguenzai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1250,1311,1810,1836]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, either under daily light, or under UV light, but the uniform milky aspect of the shell surface suggests a colourless, or lightly coloured, original condition.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[811,1457,1810,2028]" lastBlockId="7.[130,777,821,2028]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="458" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">
In addition to the variability in size and shape, another variable character was observed: some shells (about 20%) show a “false fifth plication” (
<bibRefCitation author="COOVERT G. A. &amp; COOVERT H. K." box="[1067,1353,2001,2028]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" pagination="43 - 110" refId="ref6313" refString="COOVERT G. A. &amp; COOVERT H. K. 1995. - Revision of the supraspecific classification of marginelliform gastropods. The Nautilus 109 (2 - 3): 43 - 110." type="journal article" year="1995">Coovert &amp; Coovert, 1995</bibRefCitation>
). In most cases it consists of a weak, elongate tubercle near the fourth (posterior) plication (
<figureCitation box="[350,428,853,879]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="7.[132,143,707,725]" captionTargetBox="[132,775,215,669]" captionTargetId="figure-886@7.[132,775,215,669]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIG. 6. — Marginella seguenzai n. sp.: shells with a fifth false plication (arrows): A, poorly developed fifth plication; B, well developed fifth plication. Scale bar: 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5208560" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5208560/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Fig.6A</figureCitation>
). Rarely, the false plication is more elongate and stronger, resembling a true, internally continuous, columellar plication (( 
<figureCitation box="[366,446,917,943]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="7.[132,143,707,725]" captionTargetBox="[132,775,215,669]" captionTargetId="figure-886@7.[132,775,215,669]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIG. 6. — Marginella seguenzai n. sp.: shells with a fifth false plication (arrows): A, poorly developed fifth plication; B, well developed fifth plication. Scale bar: 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5208560" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5208560/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Fig. 6B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5208560" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5208560" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5208560/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" startId="7.[132,143,707,725]" targetBox="[132,775,215,669]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph blockId="7.[132,777,707,770]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">
FIG. 6. — 
<taxonomicName authority="Perna &amp; Vazzana, 2016" authorityName="Perna &amp; Vazzana" authorityYear="2016" box="[211,383,707,725]" class="Gastropoda" family="Marginellidae" genus="Marginella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="seguenzai" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[211,383,707,725]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Marginella seguenzai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[388,437,707,725]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
: shells with a fifth false plication (arrows): 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[132,145,729,747]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">A</emphasis>
, poorly developed fifth plication; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[421,434,729,747]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">B</emphasis>
, well developed fifth plication. Scale bar: 2 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="7.[130,777,821,2028]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">
In some cases, the transition between spire and last whorl appears somewhat stepped, the spire being slightly narrower than the adjacent last whorl, as seen in 
<figureCitation box="[543,678,1012,1039]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="6.[132,143,1701,1719]" captionTargetBox="[137,1450,215,1664]" captionTargetId="figure-144@6.[136,1450,214,1664]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIG. 5. — Marginella seguenzai n. sp.: A-C, holotype, H 9.3 mm (MZB60202); D, paratype 1, H 10.6 mm (MZB60203); E-G, paratype 2, H 9.7 mm (MZB60203); H, I, paratype 3, H 9.0 mm (MZB60203); J, paratype 4, H 8.4 mm (MBMPRC); L, paratype 5, H 11.8 mm (MBMPRC). Scale bar: 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5208558" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5208558/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Figure 5H, I</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[130,777,821,2028]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">
None of the 
<taxonomicName box="[286,476,1044,1070]" class="Gastropoda" family="Marginellidae" genus="Marginella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[286,398,1044,1070]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Marginella</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
known from the Pliocene of Estepona (
<bibRefCitation author="MUNIZ SOLIS R." box="[242,434,1076,1102]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" pagination="263 - 306" refId="ref7806" refString="MUNIZ SOLIS R. 2002. - Estudio de las Familias Cystiscidae Stimpson, 1865 y Marginellidae Fleming, 1828 (Gastropoda, Neogastropoda) del Plioceno de Estepona (Malaga, Espana). Pliocenica 2: 263 - 306." type="journal article" year="2002">Muñiz Solis 2002</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="LANDAU B. &amp; LA PERNA R. &amp; MARQUET R." box="[444,655,1076,1103]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" pagination="22 - 60" refId="ref7334" refString="LANDAU B., LA PERNA R. &amp; MARQUET R. 2006 a. - The Early Pliocene Gastropoda (Mollusca) of Estepona, Southern Spain. Part 10. Marginellidae, Cystiscidae. Palaeontos 9: 22 - 60." type="journal article" year="2006">
Landau 
<emphasis box="[531,582,1076,1102]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">et al.</emphasis>
2006a
</bibRefCitation>
) is particularly similar to the new species, all markedly differing in some respects (mainly size, shape and robustness).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[130,777,821,2028]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">
Few of the many species known from Eastern Atlantic, deserve a comparison with the new species, such as 
<taxonomicName authority="Jousseaume, 1884" authorityName="Jousseaume" authorityYear="1884" class="Gastropoda" family="Marginellidae" genus="Marginella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="gloriosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Marginella gloriosa</emphasis>
Jousseaume, 1884
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Locard, 1897" authorityName="Locard" authorityYear="1897" box="[400,675,1236,1262]" class="Gastropoda" family="Marginellidae" genus="Marginella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="marocana">
<emphasis box="[400,533,1236,1261]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">M. marocana</emphasis>
Locard, 1897
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Dautzenberg, 1910" authorityName="Dautzenberg" authorityYear="1910" class="Gastropoda" family="Marginellidae" genus="Marginella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="bavay">
<emphasis box="[681,775,1236,1262]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">M. bavay</emphasis>
Dautzenberg, 1910
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Bouchet &amp; Waren, 1985" authorityName="Bouchet &amp; Waren" authorityYear="1985" box="[361,771,1267,1294]" class="Gastropoda" family="Marginellidae" genus="Marginella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="aronnax">
<emphasis box="[361,488,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">M. aronnax</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="BOUCHET P. &amp; WAREN A." box="[494,771,1267,1294]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" pagination="123 - 296" refId="ref6057" refString="BOUCHET P. &amp; WAREN A. 1985. - Revision of the Northeast Atlantic bathyal and abyssal Neogastropoda excluding Turridae (Mollusca, Gastropoda). Bollettino Malacologico suppl. 1: 123 - 296." type="journal article" year="1985">Bouchet &amp; Warén, 1985</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bozzetti, 1995)" baseAuthorityName="Bozzetti" baseAuthorityYear="1995" box="[134,470,1299,1326]" class="Gastropoda" family="Marginellidae" genus="Marginella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="colomborum">
<emphasis box="[134,296,1299,1325]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">M. colomborum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="BOZZETTI L." box="[307,462,1299,1326]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" pagination="48 - 52" refId="ref6094" refString="BOZZETTI L. 1995. - Tre nuove specie della famiglia Marginellidae Fleming, 1828 (Gastropoda, Prosobranchia) from the Indian and Atlantic Ocean. World Shells 14: 48 - 52 and errata corrige 15: 62." type="journal article" year="1995">Bozzetti, 1995</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Goud &amp; Neefs, 1996" authorityName="Goud &amp; Neefs" authorityYear="1996" class="Gastropoda" family="Marginellidae" genus="Marginella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="gilva">
<emphasis box="[520,605,1299,1325]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">M. gilva</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="GOUD J. &amp; NEEFS J." pageId="7" pageNumber="458" pagination="25 - 50" refId="ref6984" refString="GOUD J. &amp; NEEFS J. 1996. - The larger marginelliform gastropods (Cystiscidae and Marginellidae) collected during the CANCAP and MAURITANIA expeditions in the southern part of the North Atlantic Ocean. The genera Persicula, Prunum, Dentimargo, Marginella and Glabella. Vita Marina 43 (3 - 4): 25 - 50." type="journal article" year="1996">Goud &amp; Neefs, 1996</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but in most cases there are evident differences involving size and shape (convexity of spire whorls, spire elevation, shell slenderness, shape of outer lip, etc.). Of these species, only 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bozzetti" baseAuthorityYear="1995" box="[134,293,1427,1453]" class="Gastropoda" family="Marginellidae" genus="Marginella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="colomborum">
<emphasis box="[134,293,1427,1453]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">M.colomborum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shows an interesting overlap of characters with the new species. It was described from the Josephine Bank (
<bibRefCitation author="BOZZETTI L." pageId="7" pageNumber="458" pagination="48 - 52" refId="ref6094" refString="BOZZETTI L. 1995. - Tre nuove specie della famiglia Marginellidae Fleming, 1828 (Gastropoda, Prosobranchia) from the Indian and Atlantic Ocean. World Shells 14: 48 - 52 and errata corrige 15: 62." type="journal article" year="1995">Bozzetti 1995</bibRefCitation>
), a seamount in the North-East Atlantic, off Cape 
<collectingCountry box="[133,256,1523,1549]" name="Saint Vincent and the Grenadines" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">St. Vincent</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="GUBBAY S." box="[272,430,1523,1549]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" refId="ref7045" refString="GUBBAY S. 2003. - Seamounts of the North East Atlantic. WWF / OASIS, Bremen, 38 p." type="book" year="2003">Gubbay 2003</bibRefCitation>
). Though originally assigned to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Herrmannsen" authorityYear="1852" box="[238,323,1555,1580]" class="Gastropoda" family="Marginellidae" genus="Prunum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[238,323,1555,1580]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Prunum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this species must be allocated in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lamarck" authorityYear="1799" box="[132,244,1586,1612]" class="Gastropoda" family="Marginellidae" genus="Marginella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[132,244,1586,1612]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Marginella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The species was examined on three shells from the 
<typeStatus box="[131,176,1619,1645]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">type</typeStatus>
locality (
<figureCitation box="[276,337,1618,1645]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="8.[132,143,824,842]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,215,781]" captionTargetId="figure-764@8.[132,1455,214,781]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIG. 7. — Marginella colomborum (Bozzetti,1995),Josephine Bank,Seamount 1 Exp.,St.DW37,255-270 m,36°42N,14°18W,4 Oct.1988 (MNHN):A-C, H 10.0 mm; D, H 9.8 mm. Scale bar: 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5208562" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5208562/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
A-D): the shell is colourless (actually very light pinkish, with the outer lip white), height close to that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Perna &amp; Vazzana, 2016" authorityName="Perna &amp; Vazzana" authorityYear="2016" box="[160,293,1683,1708]" class="Gastropoda" family="Marginellidae" genus="Marginella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="seguenzai" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[160,293,1683,1708]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">M. seguenzai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[299,357,1683,1709]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
also in the range (12.9- 
<quantity box="[608,707,1682,1709]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.13" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" unit="mm" value="11.3">11.3 mm</quantity>
in the original description, 10.0- 
<quantity box="[406,491,1714,1741]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.8" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" unit="mm" value="8.8">8.8 mm</quantity>
in the examined material), outer lip moderately thick, making a broad curve posteriorly, as in the new species. A remarkable difference from 
<taxonomicName authority="Perna &amp; Vazzana, 2016" authorityName="Perna &amp; Vazzana" authorityYear="2016" box="[642,774,1779,1804]" class="Gastropoda" family="Marginellidae" genus="Marginella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="seguenzai" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[642,774,1779,1804]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">M. seguenzai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[132,191,1810,1836]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is the last whorl convexity, being 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bozzetti" baseAuthorityYear="1995" box="[549,713,1810,1836]" class="Gastropoda" family="Marginellidae" genus="Marginella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="colomborum">
<emphasis box="[549,713,1810,1836]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">M. colomborum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
more inflated(H/D 
<quantity box="[279,405,1841,1868]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5212" metricValueMax="4.7244" metricValueMin="4.318" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" unit="in" value="1.78" valueMax="1.86" valueMin="1.7">1.70-1.86 in</quantity>
the examined material) than the new species, apparently without overlap.The shape of the aperture, rather parallel-sided in the new species and widening anteriorly in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bozzetti" baseAuthorityYear="1995" box="[158,316,1937,1963]" class="Gastropoda" family="Marginellidae" genus="Marginella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="colomborum">
<emphasis box="[158,316,1937,1963]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">M. colomborum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is another outstanding difference. Moreover, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bozzetti" baseAuthorityYear="1995" box="[130,292,1969,1995]" class="Gastropoda" family="Marginellidae" genus="Marginella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="colomborum">
<emphasis box="[130,292,1969,1995]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">M. colomborum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has slightly convex spire whorls, whereas they are flat in the new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="458" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="7.[811,1457,215,560]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bozzetti" baseAuthorityYear="1995" box="[835,1108,215,241]" class="Gastropoda" family="Marginellidae" genus="Marginella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="colomborum">
<emphasis box="[835,1108,215,241]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Marginella colomborum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been also recorded from Seine and Ampère, other NE Atlantic seamounts (
<bibRefCitation author="BECK T. &amp; METZGER T. &amp; FREIWALD A." pageId="7" pageNumber="458" refId="ref5918" refString="BECK T., METZGER T. &amp; FREIWALD A. 2005. - BIAS. Biodiversity Inventorial Atlas of Macrobenthic Seamount Animals. OASIS, Hamburg, 118 p." type="book" year="2005">
Beck 
<emphasis box="[815,867,279,305]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">et al.</emphasis>
2005
</bibRefCitation>
). On WoRMS, 
<bibRefCitation author="GOFAS S." box="[1107,1255,279,306]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" refId="ref6793" refString="GOFAS S. 2015. - Marginella colomborum (Bozzetti, 1995) in MolluscaBase (2015). Accessed through: World Register of Marine Species at http: // www. marinespecies. org / aphia. php? p = taxdetails &amp; id = 140321 on 2015 - 07 - 17." type="url" year="2015">Gofas (2015)</bibRefCitation>
added: “Endemic of Josephine, Seine and Ampère seamounts; common on Josephine, 
<quantity box="[938,1068,343,370]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.025" metricValueMax="3.35" metricValueMin="2.7" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" unit="m" value="302.5" valueMax="335.0" valueMin="270.0">270-335 m</quantity>
, rare on Seine and Ampère; a very similar if not identical species is found in the Italian Pleistocene”. The fossil species to which Gofas refers is 
<taxonomicName authority="Perna &amp; Vazzana, 2016" authorityName="Perna &amp; Vazzana" authorityYear="2016" class="Gastropoda" family="Marginellidae" genus="Marginella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="seguenzai" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">M. seguenzai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[889,950,439,465]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, of which he had examined some shells. Gofas’ view about the close similarity between 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bozzetti" baseAuthorityYear="1995" box="[1281,1457,470,496]" class="Gastropoda" family="Marginellidae" genus="Marginella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="colomborum">
<emphasis box="[1281,1457,470,496]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">M. colomborum</emphasis>
